      "timestampEdited": null,
      "callEndedTimestamp": null,
      "isPinned": false,
      "content": "Not really ^^ \n\nGF, or rather meds-tech (the partner with which we do the submission), would like us to adhere to the DRC rules as much as possible to streamline the submission process. If there are no DRC violations, then there's nothing to waive and submission is much faster.\n\nWe did waive a number of DRC rules, mostly recommended ones, for Run 1. The metal slots are actually MR rules, so to say, but it seems they were okay with manufacturing it anyway (perhaps the violations were not that bad).",
      "author": {
        "id": "323371864074485771",
        "name": "mole99",
        "discriminator": "0000",
        "nickname": "Leo Moser (mole99)",
